3) What are the eigenvalues and associated eigenvectors if the matrix $$ A = \pmatrix{ 2 & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & -1 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 4} $$

$$ \pmatrix{A - \lambda I} = \pmatrix{2-\lambda & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & -1-\lambda & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 4-\lambda}=0 $$ $$ A $$ is upper Triangular, so eigenvalues are on the diagonal. 

$$ \therefore \lambda_1 = 2 \qquad \lambda_2 = -1 \qquad \lambda_3 = 4 $$

$$ \lambda_1 = 2, \quad  \pmatrix{ 2 - (2) & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & -1 - (2) & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 4-(2)} = \pmatrix{ 0 & 1  & 1 \\ 0 & -3 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 2 }x_1 = \pmatrix{ 0  \\ 0 \\ 0 } \implies x_1 = N(A-\lambda_1) = \pmatrix{ 1 \\ 0 \\ 0 }$$

$$ \lambda_2 = -1, \quad \pmatrix{2 - (-1) & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & -1 - (-1) & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 4-(-1)} = \pmatrix{ 3 & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 5 }x_2 = \pmatrix{ 0 \\ 0 \\ 0 } \implies x_2 = N(A-\lambda_2) = \pmatrix{ -1 \\ 3 \\ 0 }$$

$$ \lambda_3 = 4, \quad \pmatrix{2 - (4) & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & -1 - (4) & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 4-(4)} = \pmatrix{ -2 & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & -5 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 0}x_3 = \pmatrix{ 0 \\ 0 \\ 0 } \implies x_3 = N(A-\lambda_3) = \pmatrix{ 3 \\ 1 \\ 5 }$$

>   $$ \pmatrix{ 0 & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & -3 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 2}  \rightarrow \pmatrix{ 0 & 1 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 0} \implies \matrix{x_2 = 0 \\ x_3 = 0} \qquad x_1 = \alpha \qquad X = \pmatrix{\alpha \\ 0 \\ 0 } = \alpha \pmatrix{1 \\ 0 \\ 0 }$$

>   $$ \pmatrix{ 3 & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 5}  \rightarrow \pmatrix{ 3 & 1 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 0}  \implies \matrix{ \frac{1}{3}x_2 = -x_1 \\ x_3 = 0} \qquad x_1 = \alpha \qquad X = \pmatrix{ -\alpha \\ 3\alpha \\ 0} = \alpha \pmatrix{ -1 \\ 3 \\ 0}$$

>   $$ \pmatrix{ -2 & 1 & 1 \\ 0 & -5 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 0} \rightarrow \pmatrix{ 1 & 0 & -\frac{3}{5} \\ 0 & 1 & -\frac{1}{5} \\ 0 & 0 & 0} \implies \matrix{ x_1 = \frac{3}{5}x_3 \\ x_2 = \frac{1}{5}x_3} \qquad x_3 = \alpha \qquad X = \pmatrix{ \frac{3}{5}\alpha \\ \frac{1}{5}\alpha \\ \alpha}= \alpha\pmatrix{ 3 \\ 1 \\ 5 }$$


